{"fingerprint": "18a3532d895118665e04bd98f3f7230289b6449d", "package": "jac-scale", "file": "jac/jaclang/scale/config/plugin_config.jac", "rule": "dead-code", "summary": "This ~492-line file defines JacScalePluginConfig, a static schema/metadata-description class (get_plugin_metadata, get_config_schema) that re-describes every default already declared in config/impl/config_loader.impl.jac's get_default_config(), as a verbose nested dict. Grepped the whole repo for JacScalePluginConfig and found only its own declaration line \u2014 nothing imports, instantiates, or calls its static methods, including its own test suite. Sibling plugin-config classes elsewhere in the monorepo (JacMcpPluginConfig, byllm's) are exercised by jac/tests/cli/test_mcp.jac; this one has zero references anywhere. Entire file can be deleted.", "score": 1230.0, "est_loc_saved": 492, "confidence": 5, "risk": 2, "branch": "nightshift/2026-07-14/dead-plugin-config", "status": "new", "attempts": 0, "first_seen": "2026-07-14", "last_seen": "2026-07-14"}
